Twenty-five samples could not be amplified in the RT and/or PR regions due to low viral load. Therefore 303/328 patients were included in the final analysis. One hundred fifty (49.5%) individuals were male, 126 (38.4%) female, and 27 (8.9%) unknown (not reported). In terms of the disclosed transmission routes, 97 (32.0%) patients were persons who inject drugs (PWID), 82 (27.1%) were heterosexuals, 76 (25.1%) were from late-1980Â´s nosocomial infections, 32 (10.6%) were vertical infections, 8 (2.6%) were men having sex with men (MSM), and for 8 (2.6%) the transmission route was not reported. Males were significantly more often PWID (42.2% of male infections; 
 p < 0.001), whereas females were more likely to have been infected through heterosexual contact (46.8% of female infections; 
 p < 0.001) (
 Figure 1A).
